@neilcsmith-net Likely our fault but the fact is that I did not know about it, @junichi11 did not know about it. Not sure how many other PRs were/will be merged so far/yet. Where can I read about it? There is no such info on the [main repository page](https://github.com/apache/netbeans).

Regarding "unusual" - a more typical is IMHO to tag a changeset, create a release branch for it, cherry-pick fixes of serious bugs to it and release when ready. In this situation, `master` is open for any development without any "freezes". Just my two cents.

Thanks.

@tmysik No problem!  You're right it should be included on the main repository page, although the canonical place for discussion is dev@ and this was covered there, and also the agreed schedule at https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/NETBEANS/Release+Schedule

Release branching and cherry picking was what was done before, but there were a number of suggestions to move away from that in speeding up our release cycles.  It was also suggested we move towards tagging master for at least non-LTS releases, although we can't do that yet anyway.

@junichi11 did you revert? Thinking not, but there's no longer a revert button on this page either.

> By the way I'm not sure that only javadoc date and javadoc category are the element to configure per release.

